description:
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications for a Consultant Chest Radiologist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is based at York Hospital and covers work across all the associated sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post involves working within the existing team of 3 chest radiologists to report a full range of chest CT, perform lung biopsies and contribute to the lung MDT. Other subspecialist interest would be encouraged and supported though is not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have EBUS available on site. PET scans, cardiothoracic surgery, tertiary ILD and emphysema MDTS are accessed via our tertiary centres of Leeds and Hull.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role includes a commitment to general responsibilities in the department. Acute CT and MRI reporting is dealt with by a team based within in a dedicated acute reporting hub, facilitating sharing of expertise and interesting cases. All radiologists have a short weekly session as the duty radiologist. On call is currently outsourced from 9pm and plans have been approved to reduce the on call commitment further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;York Hospital has 2 MRI scanners and 3 CT scanners. Scarborough Hospital has 1 MRI scanner upgraded 2 years ago and 1 CT scanner with funding approved for a second. The Trust has recently had a £40million development approved for ED at Scarborough Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The radiology department is committed to teaching. We support radiology trainees from both Leeds and Hull rotations and the department is consistently rated highly by trainees. We have strong links with Hull York Medical School, providing opportunities in teaching and training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a cohesive and friendly department, working well as a team and with referring clinicians. There is a strong culture of sharing expertise and seeking advice. The management team is supportive and forward thinking. The department is currently embarking on a wide ranging programme of development and modernisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;York is internationally renowned for its beauty and heritage. Excellent rail and road links ensure easy access to major cities (only 2 hours to London) and to the wonderful North Yorkshire countryside. An extensive cycle network allows a pleasant, alternative commute to work. York has been recently voted as one of the best places to live in the UK. It is a lovely place to raise a family and has a plethora of excellent schools. The two universities in the city are highly renowned.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On joining the Trust you will gain access to a wide range of staff benefits. We offer a competitive relocation package of up to £8,000 and a study leave budget of £3,000 across three years will be allocated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must have a medical degree and be on the GMC Specialist Register or be within twelve months of obtaining their CCT (or equivalent) at the time of interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are an overseas candidate please contact our recruitment team to discuss opportunities for fixed term contracts if you are interested in working with us to gain your specialist registration.&lt;/p&gt;
